HOW IT ALL BEGAN
  There are many theories concerning the actual dis-
covery of glass-a caveman, extinguishing his fire, may
have noticed that the ash and silica had fused, forming
a hard, solid substance-a nomad on the desert may have
had the same experience. In Biblical times and during
the Roman era, glass beads were valued as jewels. Even
our early settlers traded valuable glass beads for land.
For centuries, men have been aware that glass could
be drawn into filaments of exceptional strength. At first
these filaments were used to beautify beads and vases.


  RALPH SMITH, a sophomore C.E., was a draftsman
