 however, a new and unquestionably more fair system of
 scoring has been developed. Based on probability and
 statistics, this system of scoring will make it possible for
 any department, regardless of its size, to have an equal op-
 portunity to win any event. This scoring system can be
 briefly described as follows: Each event will be judged in
 such a manner so that a mean may be obtained. Statistical
 theory predicts that each department will be positioned a
 certain number of standard deviations on one side or the
 other of the mean department. The next step in the scor-
 ing is to translate the standard deviations units into points.
 This is accomplished by fixing the number of possible
 points for one event. Since all other events are scored with
 respect to this particular event, their maximum number
 of points are automatically fixed. Each department is then
 judged in each event and the winners determined. This
 system will certainly eliminate all of the inconsistencies
 which have existed in the previous scoring methods.
